<h3>
2.1.  User Interface Overview
</h3>
</a>
<p>
When the user initially invokes the Test Tool, the screen appears as shown
in Figure 1-1.

<br>
<br>
<hr>
<a name="Figure Initial screen">
<a name="Initial screen">
<p align=center>
<img src="images/login.png">
</p>
</a>
<p align=center> Figure 1-1:  Login Screen.  </p>
<hr>
</a>
<br>

<p>The user logs in with their credentials and is given access to the program.

<p>Test Takers get taken to the Test Taking section, which is further explained in 
<a href="test-taking.html">Section 2.5 Test Taking</a> 

<p>Test Makers and Test Proctors get taken to the starting screen which is shown in Figure 1-2.


<br>
<br>
<hr>
<a name="Figure Expanded menus tab">
<a name="Expanded menus tab">
<p align=center>
<img src="images/initial-screen.png">
</p>
</a>
<p align=center> Figure 1-2:  Initial Screen.  </p>
<hr>
</a>
<br>

<p>The slider on the right slide opens up a tab of menus to the other available sections as 
shown in Figure 1-3.

<br>
<br>
<hr>
<a name="Figure Expanded menus tab">
<a name="Expanded menus tab">
<p align=center>
<img src="images/initial-screen-2.png">
</p>
</a>
<p align=center> Figure 1-3:  Expanded Menus Tab.  </p>
<hr>
</a>
<br>

<p> This figure illustrates the sections available to the Test Maker. Test Proctors will have
a similar looking tab, but will be limited to the Teacher and Statistics sections, with the rest of 
the sections being greyed out.

<p> The Menu tab can be hidden again by clicking on the protruding tab.
The current section that the user is in is highlighted in yellow.



<p>
<tt>Test Cr.</tt> takes you to the Test Creation page. This is explained in 
<a href="test-creation.html">Section 2.1 Test Creation</a>.
<p>
The <tt>Test Bank</tt> section contains the lists of questions stored, as well as previously created
tests. The questions can be searched for by a range of categories, such as difficulty, subject, 
and date created. This is further explained in <a href="gen-test-revise.html">Section 2.2.3 Revising Tests and Editing Settings</a>.
<p>
<tt> Q. Bank </tt> takes you to the Question Bank, where all saved questions are stored. These can be arranged
by course, subject, difficulty, and more. This is further explained in <a href="edit-ques.html">Section 2.3.5 Editing an Existing Question</a> 
<p>
The <tt>Teacher</tt> section contains the teacher functions for tests. These functions include adding 
and deleting users allowed to take the tests, grading non-automated-grader questions, publishing grades, 
viewing student information, and toggling on/off whether a test is still active. This is further explained in 
<a href="teach-func.html">Section 2.6 Teacher Functions</a>.
<p>
The <tt>Statistics</tt> section is where test information is held. This information includes test averages, 
individual student scores, students' number of attempts, and which questions they missed. A more thorough explanation
can be found in <a href="statistics.html">Section 2.5 Statistics</a>.  

